GraphML test files exercising XML data/character encoding edge cases.
They check how a GraphML parser copes with tricky characters and whitespace in the markup.

The diagram content is a trimmed-down excerpt of "FlexsimObject OnDraw Event Dispatching"
(FlexsimObjectOnDrawDispatching.graphml), reduced to a single table node with two flowchart
nodes so the encoding case under test is easy to see. The original diagrams come from the
FlexSim Module SDK documentation.

ddot.it/this ..kind.. synthetic (trimmed from collected source)
ddot.it/this ..format.. format:graphml-1.1

data-enc-apos.graphml.xml ..tests.. apostrophes (') inside node-label text content, plus raw line breaks within the label text
data-linebreaks.graphml.xml ..tests.. line breaks between attributes inside an XML start tag (the <graphml> element split across multiple lines)
